Informed Consent for Participation in Research Activities

Project Title:  Decisions, Games and Markets

Principal Investigator: Marcos Gallo; Address: MC 228-77, California Institute of Technology, Pasadena, CA 91125; Phone: 626-395-2856; Email: mnazaret@caltech.edu

Purpose of this Research Study:  

The purpose of this study is research.  This is not a clinical study and we do not provide medical treatment. Our main purpose is to understand how people perceive others. 

While we are happy to talk to you more about the scientific findings of our work, we will not give you any feedback. This means we cannot tell you how you compare to other people on any measures.

The study will take approximately 20-25 minutes.

If you have any questions about any part of the study or this informed consent, please ask the researcher.  Questions are encouraged.

Background:

 

This project aims to understand how resource scarcity, particularly related to time, will impact the time it takes to complete a particular set of tasks. Likewise, we aim to assess how many tasks will remain uncompleted at the end of a particular period of time. 

 

Who Can Participate:

 

Any person over 18 years of age residing in the US is eligible to participate.

 

What Will Be Done:   

 

In this survey, you will choose to complete ice-cream orders. In the experimental procedure, participants will be hosting their own ice cream parlor with two different potential orders. Each order will have an associated value. For every order completed, you will earn the dollar amount associated with that order. As more orders arrive as time progresses, the participant must decide what tasks to attend to. If some tasks are not completed within a timely manner, that order might “leave” the parlor.

Possible Risks and Discomforts: 

 

The risks or discomforts to you as a result of participating in the study are minimal. The testing may result in mild fatigue, boredom, and or frustration with the survey. These risks are no more than might be expected when performing any other psychological survey.

 

Collaborative Study/Sharing Research Data:

Possible Benefits: 

You personally will not benefit directly from participation in this research study in any way.  This research may help extend our understanding of how people perceive others.

Alternatives: 

Your alternative is to choose not to participate in this study.

Compensation:

You are entitled to compensation for participating in this experiment. Your compensation will be $1 for participation plus up to $2 depending on your performance in the game.

 

Withdrawal from Study:

 

Your participation is voluntary.  If you first agree to participate and then you change your mind, you are free to withdraw your consent and discontinue your participation in this study at any time.  Your decision will not affect your relationship, if any, with Caltech and you will not be penalized or lose any benefits to which you would otherwise be entitled. 

To withdraw from the study, you only need to let the experimenter know (or tell a 17th Door staff member as you go through the tour by saying “Unplug”). You will not be asked to explain your reasons. Subjects can withdraw and any point during the experiment.  They will be paid in full and their data will be destroyed.

We may also withdraw you from the study without your consent for scientific or technical reasons.  We will not be able to give you detailed explanations of the reasons. 

Confidentiality of Records: 

Any information from this study in which you might be identified will be confidential. By signing this form, however, you allow the study investigators to make your records available to the Caltech Institutional Review Board Office and regulatory or funding agencies as required by law. If the information generated by this study is published, you will never be identified by name.

Data collected from this study will be kept in Colin Camerer’s laboratory at the California Institute of Technology.  We will take reasonable steps to ensure that no unauthorized person will have access to the data generated by this study. Digital data will be password protected.

Offer to Answer Questions and Research Injury Notification: 

The Caltech researchers have offered to answer any and all questions regarding your participation in this research study. If you have any further questions or in the event of a research-related injury, you can contact the principal investigator at 626-395-2856 (Marcos Gallo), or the Caltech Institutional Review Board Administrator at (626)395-4699 or at irb@caltech.edu.

 

Voluntary Participation with Right of Refusal: 

You have been informed that your participation in this research study is voluntary. You are free to withdraw your consent for participation in any part of this study without any penalty.

IRB Review and Impartial Third Party: 

This study has been reviewed and approved by the Institutional Review Board (IRB) of the California Institute of Technology. A representative of that board, from the IRB Office, is available to discuss the review process or your rights as a research subject. The telephone number of the IRB office is 626-3954699 and their email is irb@caltech.edu.

Sponsor of this Research: 

N/A

You have carefully read the information contained above in the "Experimental Subject's Bill of Rights" and understand fully your rights as a potential subject in a research experiment involving people as subjects.
